.SH "NAME"
debugfs_remove_recursive \- recursively removes a directory
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'void\ debugfs_remove_recursive('u
.BI "void debugfs_remove_recursive(struct\ dentry\ *\ " "dentry" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIdentry\fR
.RS 4
a pointer to a the dentry of the directory to be removed\&. If this parameter is NULL or an error value, nothing will be done\&.
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
This function recursively removes a directory tree in debugfs that was previously created with a call to another debugfs function (like
\fBdebugfs_create_file\fR
or variants thereof\&.)
.PP
This function is required to be called in order for the file to be removed, no automatic cleanup of files will happen when a module is removed, you are responsible here\&.
